1 Download Ubuntu Server Iso From https://ubuntu.com/download/server
2 Select Ubuntu Server Iso You Want LTS Or Interim (LTS Is Recommended)
3 Setup Ubuntu Server
4 Run sudo nano /etc/issue then change Ubuntu And Its Version To ExpertOS
  Run sudo nano /etc/issue.net Also Change Ubuntu And Its Version To ExpertOS
5 Run sudo nano /etc/os-release
  Change PRETTY_NAME="Ubuntu And Its Version" To PRETTY_NAME="ExpertOS"
  Change NAME="Ubuntu" To NAME"ExpertOS"
  Change VERSION_ID="Ubuntu Version" To VERSION_ID=""
  Change VERSION="Ubuntu Version" To VERSION=""
  Change VERSION_CODENAME=ubuntu codename to VERSION_CODENAME=
  Change ID=ubuntu to ID=expertos
  Change HOME_URL="https://ubuntu.com/" To HOME_URL="https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/ExpertOS"
6 Update initramfs with sudo update-initramfs -u sudo update-grub and sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
7 Show Grub Menu (If You Need It)
  Run sudo nano /etc/default/grub
  Then
  GRUB_TIMEOUT_STYLE=menu
  GRUB_TIMEOUT=5
  Then sudo update-grub
8 Run sudo nano /etc/grub.d/10_linux
  Then Change OS=GNU/Linux To OS=
  Also Change OS="${GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR} GNU/Linux"
  To OS="${GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR}"
  Then sudo update-grub
9 Install A Graphical Environment (If You Need It)
   1 Install Cinnamon Its Default Desktop Environment For ExpertOS sudo apt install cinnamon -y
   2 sudo systemctl enable lightdm
     sudo systemctl start lightdm
   3 Change Debian Wallpaper To Default Adwaita Background By Click Right Mouse Then Change Desktop Background Then Change It To Adwaita Then Select Adwaita Wallpaper
   After You Install A Graphical Environment
   Install konqueror with sudo apt install konqueror
   Open Konqueror Then Go To https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/ExpertOS
   Then Download ExpertOS Logo In readme then rename 544848239-19e7fa44-d470-4fc8-81b8-2ff8783859a7.png To expertos-logo.png Then Save It To Downloads
   Then Run sudo mv /home/yourusername/Downloads/expertos-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps
   Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/expertos-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/ubuntu-logo.svg
   Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/expertos-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/ubuntu-logo-text.png
   Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/expertos-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/ubuntu-logo-text-dark.png
   Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/expertos-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/debian-logo.png
   Then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/expertos-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/debian-security.png
   Then Enable System Sounds By Clicking Enable On Sounds Open Sounds
   Then Set Cinnamon Login To Changing The Sound Volume On Then Add sound With freedesktop then stereo then select sounds
   servive-login.oga
   -Starting Cinnamon
   servive-logout.oga
   -Leaving Cinnamon
   windows-attention.oga
   -Switching Workspace
   -Opening new windows
   -Closing windows
   -Minimizing windows
   -Maximizing windows
   -Unmaximizing windows
   -Tiling and snapping windows
   -device-added.oga
   Inserting a device
   device-removed.oga
   -Removing a device
   message.oga
   -Showing notifications
   audio-volume-change.oga
   -Changing the sound volume
   Go To Menu Then On Appearance Click Use a custom icon and label
10 Setting A Plymouth Theme (Graphical Environment Only)
   if plymouth isnt installed run sudo apt install plymouth plymouth-themes
   then sudo nano /etc/default/grub then add quiet splash or change quiet to quiet splash then sudo update-grub
   sudo update-alternatives --install /usr/share/plymouth/themes/default.plymouth default.plymouth /usr/share/plymouth/themes/joy/joy.plymouth 100
   sudo update-alternatives --config default.plymouth
   Then Select Joy
   BEFORE YOU UPDATE INITRAMFS YOU MUST CHANGE DEBIAN LOGO TO EXPERTOS LOGO BY RUNNING THESE COMMANDS
   sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/expertos-logo.png /usr/share/plymouth/themes/joy/debian_logo.png
   sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/expertos-logo.png /usr/share/plymouth/themes/joy/debian_logo16.png
   Then sudo update-initramfs -u
11 Install Copilot (Recommended)
   Run sudo snap install copilot-desktop
   Then Add To Panel Then Move Copilot To positioned directly before the file manager icon

12 Have Fun And Start Using ExpertOS Then You Can Say I USE ExpertOS BTW
   
